10. Implementation
Frontend Implementation
Multiple JSP pages were created for different modules. Iframe was used to link pages without full page reload, providing a smooth single-page-like experience. Input forms were designed with validation.
Backend Implementation
ASPX pages receive POST requests from JSP. The code-behind (ASPX.CS) processes data, loads required SPICE kernels, calls appropriate SPICE functions (especially Geometry Finder routines), and returns computed results.
Database Implementation
MySQL tables were designed to store user inputs, computation requests, and result sets for traceability.
Integration
Frontend communicates with backend via form submission or AJAX. Backend triggers SPICE computations and saves results before displaying them.

